      "writtenOn": "2020-03-17T19:01:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve noticed that in a lot of places you log errors instead of returning them. i think this can lead to very confusing behavior, e.g. a program finished successfully, but actually didn\u0027t do its job. I recommend defaulting to returning errors, and switching to logging if and only if it is really OK to ignore the error. For example, this error is not ignorable. this should have been prevented in validation. I think a panic would be more appropriate",
